# RelatedPosts: Tighten spacing + add excerpt to cards

## Context

Two follow-up issues after the initial UI refinement:
1. **Too much dead space** тАФ `.cv-body` has `margin-bottom: 80px`, plus `.rp-section` adds `margin-top: 2.5rem` (40px), totaling ~145px before related posts appear. Users may not scroll far enough to see them.
2. **Cards lack content preview** тАФ Cards only show title + author/date metadata. The API already returns the full `content` field (Lexical JSON state) but it's unused. Adding a 1-line text excerpt gives users a reason to click.

## Files to modify

| File | What |
|---|---|
| `client/src/components/Discovery/RelatedPosts.jsx` | Add excerpt extraction + render excerpt line |
| `client/src/components/Discovery/RelatedPosts.css` | Reduce margin-top, add excerpt styles, update skeleton height |

## Changes

### 1. Reduce spacing тАФ `RelatedPosts.css`

Change `.rp-section` `margin-top` from `2.5rem` тЖТ `0`. The `80px` margin-bottom on `.cv-body` already provides plenty of breathing room. Removing `.rp-section`'s own margin makes the related posts feel connected to the article rather than floating in empty space.

Also reduce `padding-top` from `1.5rem` тЖТ `1rem` for a slightly tighter feel.

At 480px breakpoint: `margin-top: 0`, `padding-top: 0.75rem`.

### 2. Extract plain text from Lexical JSON тАФ `RelatedPosts.jsx`

Add a small helper function inside the file (no new file needed):

```js
function extractExcerpt(content, maxLen = 120) {
    if (!content) return '';
    try {
        const root = typeof content === 'string' ? JSON.parse(content) : content;
        const texts = [];
        const walk = (node) => {
            if (node.text) texts.push(node.text);
            if (node.children) node.children.forEach(walk);
        };
        walk(root.root || root);
        const full = texts.join(' ').replace(/\s+/g, ' ').trim();
        if (full.length <= maxLen) return full;
        return full.slice(0, maxLen).replace(/\s+\S*$/, '') + 'тАж';
    } catch {
        return '';
    }
}
```

This recursively walks the Lexical node tree, concatenates all `text` nodes, and truncates with an ellipsis at word boundaries.

### 3. Render excerpt in RelatedPostCard тАФ `RelatedPosts.jsx`

In `RelatedPostCard`, call `extractExcerpt(post.content)` and render it between the title and meta:

```jsx
{excerpt && <p className="rp-card-excerpt">{excerpt}</p>}
```

### 4. Excerpt CSS тАФ `RelatedPosts.css`

Add `.rp-card-excerpt` after `.rp-card-title`:

```css
.rp-card-excerpt {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.4;
    margin: 0 0 0.375rem 0;
    display: -webkit-box;
    -webkit-line-clamp: 1;
    -webkit-box-orient: vertical;
    overflow: hidden;
}
```

### 5. Update skeleton тАФ `RelatedPosts.css`

- Bump `.rp-skeleton-card` height from `68px` тЖТ `82px` to account for the new excerpt line
- Add a `.rp-skeleton-excerpt` shimmer bar (height 10px, width 85%) between the title and meta skeleton elements

Add the skeleton excerpt element in `RelatedPosts.jsx`'s `RelatedPostsSkeleton` too.

